Snapshots of cairo and glitz for mozilla usage.

We only include the relevant parts of each release (generally, src/*.[ch]), as
we have moz.build files used by the Mozilla build system. For documentation and
similar, please see the official tarballs at http://www.cairographics.org/.

VERSIONS:

  cairo (1.18.4)
  pixman (0.46.4)

==== Updating and Patching Cairo ====

To change Cairo in Mozilla Central, do not simply commit changes to
`gfx/cairo/cairo`, or they will be overwritten the next time Cairo is
revendored. First, commit your changes to the `firefox` branch at
`github.com/FirefoxGraphics/cairo`. Then, run this command at the top of the
Firefox source tree:

    mach vendor gfx/cairo/moz.yaml -r firefox

That checks out the `firefox` branch, makes our standard adjustments, and then
updates `gfx/cairo/cairo` accordingly. See `gfx/cairo/moz.yaml` for details.

To vendor in a new release of Cairo:

- Push appropriate branches and tags from the upstream Cairo repo to
  `github.com/FirefoxGraphics/cairo`.

- Rebase the `firefox` branch on the Cairo release you'd like to use
  as the base for Firefox.

- At the top of the Firefox source tree, run:

      mach vendor gfx/cairo/moz.yaml -r firefox

  This should change the vendored Cairo sources in `gfx/cairo/cairo` to match
  what you have committed to the `firefox` branch.

Note: Do not try to simply push all upstream tags and branches to
`github.com/FirefoxGraphics/cairo`. Some prior releases of Cairo seem to have
malformed commit blobs, and you'll get errors like this:

    missingSpaceBeforeDate: invalid author/committer line - missing space before date

Instead, just push the tags/branches you actually need.

==== pixman patches ====

pixman-armasm.patch: add an ifdef guard around pixman-config.h include

pixman-export.patch: make sure pixman symbols are not exported in libxul

pixman-interp.patch: use lower quality interpolation by default on mobile

pixman-rename.patch: include pixman-rename.h for renaming of external symbols
